This paper deals with the problem of controlling the beaconing rate in vehicular networks, which is a subfield of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper proposes a decentralized algorithm to solve the Network Utility Maximization (NUM) problem, which involves optimization and control theory (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the notion of fairness in beaconing rate allocation, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY). The algorithm uses a scaled gradient projection method, which is a technique in optimization and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents simulation results to validate the proposed approach, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA).
